# Marketing site — change only on explicit request

**Marketing** = `apps/marketing/` (deploys to **vehicleos.app**).

**Owner app** = `apps/web/` (deploys to **app.vehicleos.app**).

## Agent must

- **Never** edit `apps/marketing/**` unless the user **explicitly** asks for marketing site changes (copy, layout, pages, marketing CSS, etc.).
- **Never** replace or slim down `packages/ui/tokens.css` for owner-app work — that file is the **marketing** token source; owner app uses `apps/web/app/globals.css` (Tailwind).
- When doing owner-app UX/UI, scope changes to `apps/web/**` and app-specific packages only.
- If a shared package would affect marketing, **split** exports (marketing vs app) instead of overwriting marketing tokens.

## User said no marketing changes

Treat as default until they say otherwise: app UX work must not alter vehicleos.app appearance.
